"a.鬼鬼祟祟的 【英】 adj.鬼鬼祟祟的(acti ng or doing something clandestinely) 【考】 反义词：barefaced( 公然的); aboveboard(光明正大 的) 【记】 sur(在…下面)+rept( 爬)+itious→在下面 爬→偷偷爬(进来) 【例】 a surreptitious glance / a surreptitious meeting adj. 鬼鬼祟祟的 = secret 【记】sur下面, rept = creep爬, itious－在下面爬来爬去－偷偷的 【反】barefaced(adj 不隐瞒的); aboveboard(adj 光明正大的) 【记】sur sub 下面 + reptile 爬虫，在下面爬的 surreptitious (adj.)  mid-15c., from Latin surrepticius ""stolen, furtive, clandestine,"" from surreptus, past participle of surripere ""seize secretly, take away, steal, plagiarize,"" from assimilated form of sub ""from under"" (hence, ""secretly;"" see sub-) + rapere ""to snatch"" (see rapid). Related: Surreptitiously."
